text: Aisne may refer to: *Aisne, a French department named after: **Aisne (river), left tributary of the river Oise *Aisne River, Belgium, tributary of the river Ourthe *Aisne's 1st constituency, a French legislative constituency in the Aisne département *Battle of the Aisne (disambiguation), three different battles during World War I *Canal latéral à l'Aisne, a canal in northern France, which connects Vieux-lès-Asfeld to Celles-sur-Aisne *, a British coaster in service from 1950 to 1960 *, a cargo ship ordered by Compagnie Générale Transatlantique during World War I but requisitioned on completion by the United States Shipping Board
